Barcelona secured its first away victory of the season in all competitions with victory over Villarreal. Barcelona struck twice late on to snatch all three points from a spirited Villarreal side in La Liga. Frenkie De Jong’s close-range finish opened the scoring, but Barca were clinging on after Super Eagles forward, Samuel Chukwueze’s well-taken leveller in the 76th minute. Also Read: Chelsea Demolish Juve To Reach Champions League Last 16 However, against the run of play, Memphis Depay pounced after the Villarreal defence failed to clear a long clearance in the 88th minute. Substitute Philippe Coutinho slotted an injury-time penalty to make sure of the result. Barcelona remain seventh in the Spanish top flight. 